Description:
    Creates named module Sass and HAML files in the appropiate directories

Example:
    rails g module bar

    This will create:
        app/views/shared/modules/foo
        app/views/shared/modules/foo/readme.md
        app/views/shared/modules/foo/_bar.html.haml
        app/assets/stylesheets/modules/foo/bar
        app/assets/stylesheets/modules/foo/bar/_extend.sass
        app/assets/stylesheets/modules/foo/bar/_mixin.scss
        app/assets/stylesheets/modules/foo/bar/readme.md
        app/assets/stylesheets/modules/foo/bar/_bar.sass
        app/assets/stylesheets/_modules.sass